wikipedia_page.main: Brigadier-General Henry Edmund Burleigh Leach, CB, CMG, CVO (18 July 1870 – 16 August 1936) was a British Army officer.

response: Henry Leach was born the third son of John Leach, a naval officer, and Evelyn Burrell Leach (née Lee). He was educated at St Peter's Court, Broadstairs, and the Royal Naval College, Dartmouth.
In 2004, it was announced that the new Navy Command Headquarters building of the Royal Navy at Whale Island, Portsmouth, was to be named the "Sir Henry Leach Building" in his honour.
* Henry Leach (British Army officer) (1870–1936), British Army general
* Sir Henry Leach (1923–2011), Royal Navy admiral

After serving in the First World War, he was placed on the retired list at his own request in December 1919, at which point he held the rank of lieutenant commander. Although retired, he was made a commander in April 1923. Leach died at Eastbourne in November 1969. His brother Henry Leach was a Brigadier-General in the army.
